{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":18315,"name":"","username":"slapin","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/s/dfb087/{size}.png","created_at":"2017-06-02T07:41:00.076Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eHow would you check that Vector2 point is inside Vector polygon?\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eI mean polygons. Concave ones. I need this for some growth algorithm.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":1,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-06-02T07:41:00.076Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":24,"reads":30,"readers_count":29,"score":126.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":3189,"topic_slug":"point-inside-polygon","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":554,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":18320,"name":"Eugene Kozlov","username":"Eugene","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/eugene/{size}/902_2.png","created_at":"2017-06-02T11:37:12.465Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eHave you tried that nice algo from wiki?\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003caside class=\"onebox wikipedia\"\u003e\n  \u003cheader class=\"source\"\u003e\n      \u003ca href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Point_in_polygon\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"\u003een.wikipedia.org\u003c/a\u003e\n  \u003c/header\u003e\n  \u003carticle class=\"onebox-body\"\u003e\n    \u003cdiv class=\"aspect-image\" style=\"--aspect-ratio:220/195;\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8f/Simple_polygon.svg/220px-Simple_polygon.svg.png\" class=\"thumbnail\"\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Point_in_polygon\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"\u003ePoint in polygon\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eIn computational geometry, the point-in-polygon (PIP) problem asks whether a given point in the plane lies inside, outside, or on the boundary of a polygon. It is a special case of point location problems and finds applications in areas that deal with processing geometrical data, such as computer graphics, computer vision, geographical information systems (GIS), motion planning, and CAD. An early description of the problem in computer graphics shows two common approaches (ray casting and angle su...\u003c/p\u003e\n\n  \u003c/article\u003e\n  \u003cdiv class=\"onebox-metadata\"\u003e\n    \n    \n  \u003c/div\u003e\n  \u003cdiv style=\"clear: both\"\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003c/aside\u003e\n\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":2,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-06-02T11:37:12.465Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":1,"reads":26,"readers_count":25,"score":15.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":3189,"topic_slug":"point-inside-polygon","display_username":"Eugene Kozlov","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Point_in_polygon","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"Point in polygon - Wikipedia","clicks":7}],"read":true,"user_title":"Core developer","title_is_group":false,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":484,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":18324,"name":"","username":"slapin","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/s/dfb087/{size}.png","created_at":"2017-06-02T15:37:04.895Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eNah, that is too complicated.\u003cbr\u003e\nI use one found somewhere else:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode\u003ebool PointInPolygon(Vector2 point, Array\u0026lt;Vector2\u0026gt; points)\n{\n        int i, j, nvert = points.length;\n        bool c = false;\n\n        j = nvert - 1;\n        for (i = 0; i \u0026lt; nvert; j = i++) {\n                if (((points[i].y \u0026gt;= point.y ) != (points[j].y \u0026gt;= point.y) ) \u0026amp;\u0026amp;\n                        (point.x \u0026lt;= (points[j].x - points[i].x) * (point.y -\n                        points[i].y) / (points[j].y - points[i].y) + points[i].x))\n                        c = !c;\n        }\n        return c;\n}\n\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003cp\u003ebut was hoping there was something internal in Urho.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":3,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-06-02T15:37:04.895Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":2,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":22,"readers_count":21,"score":19.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":3189,"topic_slug":"point-inside-polygon","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"reply_to_user":{"username":"Eugene","name":"Eugene Kozlov","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/eugene/{size}/902_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":1}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":554,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false}],"stream":[18315,18320,18324]},"timeline_lookup":[[1,2000]],"suggested_topics":[{"id":7092,"title":"Finding th